Apollo Global Management  and CVC
Capital Partners Ltd. are planning to make a formal takeover
offer tomorrow for  Brit Insurance Holdings NV , the Sunday Times
reported, without saying where it got the information.  The total value of the bid will be between 851 million
pounds ($1.3 billion) and 871 million pounds, the Times said.  The private equity firms agreed to pay 10.45 pounds a share
and honor the 30 pence a share dividend to all investors, as
well as pay an extra 25 pence a share depending on the insurerâ€™s
financial performance at the end of the year, the newspaper
